# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  oudfinder.de — environment variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development, and configure the
#  same variables in your Vercel project (Settings → Environment Variables)
#  for the deployed site.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Shared secret protecting /admin/* and /api/admin/* routes.
# Generate a long random string, e.g.
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
#
# • In production this MUST be set, otherwise the middleware fails closed
#   with HTTP 503.
# • In local dev you can leave it unset — the middleware then allows
#   access without a login (so you don't have to type a password while
#   iterating on /admin/images).
ADMIN_TOKEN=
